heaviest_rainfall.status: On 04 January 2025, a record rainfall of 36.8mm was measured, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  4.6mm per hour was recorded as falling at times during the 37.2 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: Today, the rain fell at an intense rate peaking at 11.8mm per hour, one of the heaviest downpours recorded and ranked 5th from our records.  The precipitation lasted 2.1 hours and dumped 7.28mm in total.  27.0mm per hour is the maximum rain rate ever recorded on 02 September 2025, during a 15.0 hour storm which dumped 21.19mm of rain from the clouds.
